FOURTH DISTRICT.

No. 48.Rockford Ins. Co. v. Michael O’Connor.Opinion filed Nov. 27, 1885.A suit commenced by appellee against appellant to recover pay for services rendered as an agent of the company. The court being of opinion that the verdict is sustained both as to the finding of the facts and the amount found to be due the plaintiff, the judgment is affirmed.Attorneys for appellant, Messrs. Marshall & Taggart;for appellee Messrs. Hat & Knispel.

Opinion by Pills .jury, P. J. Judge below, Amos Watts.
